               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i0">
                     <locus from="1r" to="7r">1r-7r</locus>
                     <textLang xml:lang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <title type="acephalous" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT0049IHA#s13IHA">قران, Sixth ǧuz’ (6/30)</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar">
                        <locus target="#1r">-1r</locus>فَتُقُبِّلَ مِنْ أَحَدِهِمَا وَلَمْ يُتَقَبَّلْ مِنَ الْأَخَرِ </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar">
                        <locus target="#7r">-7r</locus>ذَلِكَ بأَنَّ مِنْهُمْ قِسِّيْسِيْنَ وَرُهْبَاناً وِّاَنِّهُمْ لَايَسْتَكْبِرُوْنَ<note>وِّاَنِّهُمْ is vocalized this way.</note>
                     </explicit>
                     <note>5:27-5:82. The text begins in the middle of verse 5:27. Skilled hand (good sample 4r), extended curves of final letters.  Red triple dots as verse markers. Ihmāl marks (rā'). Some words left incomplete at the end of a line, without diacritic or vocalization, and written in full on the following line. Ruler's marks (7v). Catchwords by a skilled hand.</note>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
